         <div xml:id="alalal-e11942"><!-- l3d3a19 -->
            <head xml:id="alalal-e11942-Hd1e99">Articulus 19</head>
            <head xml:id="alalal-e11942-Hd1e101" type="question-title">An caro Christi fuerit ex purissimis
sanguinibus ?</head>
            <p xml:id="alalal-e11942-d1e104">
               <cb ed="#Bd" n="b"/>
               <lb ed="Bd" n="38"/>ARTICULUS XIX,.
<lb ed="Bd" n="39"/>An caro Christi fuerit ex purissimis
<lb ed="Bd" n="40"/>sanguinibus ?
</p>
            <p xml:id="alalal-e11942-d1e115">
               <lb ed="Bd" n="41"/>Deinde, quaeritur de hoc quod dicit
<lb ed="Bd" n="42"/>ibi, A, versus medium, quod <quote xml:id="alalal-e11942-Qd1e121">copulavit
<lb ed="Bd" n="43"/>sibiipst ex sanctissimis et purissimis
<lb ed="Bd" n="44"/>sanguinibus, etc. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="alalal-e11942-d1e129">
               <lb ed="Bd" n="45"/>Ex hoc enim videtur, quod ut de 
ma<lb break="no" ed="Bd" n="46"/>teria Christus sit ex sanguine.
</p>
            <p xml:id="alalal-e11942-d1e137">
               <lb ed="Bd" n="47"/>ConTRA :
<lb ed="Bd" n="48"/>1. Augustinus infra dicit, quod ex
<lb ed="Bd" n="49"/>carne.
</p>
            <p xml:id="alalal-e11942-d1e146">
               <lb ed="Bd" n="50"/>2. Praterea, Vicinior est caro ad 
car<lb break="no" ed="Bd" n="51"/>nem quam caro ad sanguinem, vel e 
con<lb break="no" ed="Bd" n="52"/>verso ; sed habentium symbolum facilior
<lb ed="Bd" n="53"/>est unio: ergo congrucntius fuit 
assume<lb break="no" ed="Bd" n="54"/>re excarne quam ex sanguine. Sed si hoc
<lb ed="Bd" n="55"/>dicatur, tunc etiam oportuit sumere ex
<lb ed="Bd" n="56"/>ossibus ogsa, ex nervis nervos, et sic de
<lb ed="Bd" n="57"/>aliis.
</p>
            <p xml:id="alalal-e11942-d1e166">
               <lb ed="Bd" n="58"/>Solutio Dicendum, quod ex 
purissi<lb break="no" ed="Bd" n="59"/>mis sanguinibus accepit: quia sanguis
<lb ed="Bd" n="60"/>est potentia totum corpus, non autem
<lb ed="Bd" n="61"/>caro.
</p>
            <p xml:id="alalal-e11942-d1e177">
               <lb ed="Bd" n="62"/>Ad picrum Augustini dicendum, quod 
<lb ed="Bd" n="63"/>intelligit carnem pro eo quod est materia
<lb ed="Bd" n="64"/>earnis : et hoc est sanguis,
</p>
            <p xml:id="alalal-e11942-d1e186">
               <lb ed="Bd" n="65"/>Ad aliud dicendum, quod caro carni
<lb ed="Bd" n="66"/>vicinior est in forma speciei: sed non in
<lb ed="Bd" n="67"/>via generationis: quia non ex carne fit
<lb ed="Bd" n="68"/>caro, nisi corrumpatur in cibis, et per
<lb ed="Bd" n="69"/>digestionem in sanguinem convertatur,
<lb ed="Bd" n="70"/>et tunc tandem generetur inde caro. Ex
<lb ed="Bd" n="71"/>sanguine autem statim fit caro per 
con<lb break="no" ed="Bd" n="72"/>versionem et formationem generative
<lb ed="Bd" n="73"/>virtutis, vel etiam nutritive in 
quibus<lb break="no" ed="Bd" n="74"/>dam.
</p>
         </div>
